{"key":"processedPost-8891058","value":{"id":8891058,"first":8890767,"last":8904681,"when":1220817414,"utime":"09/07/08 10:56 PM","content":"The first thing you need to do is separate them from those wet rocks.&nbsp; They're trying to colonize them and that inhibits fruiting.<br /><br />Second, when they pin on the bottom only, it indicates low humidity and/or dry cakes.&nbsp; Since they want to pin in 100% humidity, right close to the damp rocks is the only place they're finding the right conditions.<br /><br />Get some foil or something larger than you have to separate them from what's below.&nbsp; Mist more often, and soak the cakes in water for 24 hours after the flush.<br /><br />I'd suggest getting rid of the hydroton and replacing it with damp, well drained perlite.&nbsp; Perlite has about 1000 times the surface area and will provide far better humidification.<br />RR","title":"Re: pinning from the bottom but not tops?BRF cake"}}